===Etymology===
From Spanish ''[[tolteca#Spanish|tolteca]]'', from Nahuatl ''[[toltecah|tōltēcah]]'', plural of ''[[toltecatl|tōltēcatl]]'' "inhabitant of Tollan", from ''[[Tollan|Tōllān]]'' + ''[[-catl]]''.
===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl='''[[Toltecs]]''' or '''[[Toltec]]'''}}

# A member of a [[Pre-Columbian]] [[Native American]] people who dominated much of central [[Mexico]] between the 10th and 12th centuries AD.
